WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

2
00:03:57.529 --> 00:03:59.197
The battle...

3
00:04:00.699 --> 00:04:01.867
It is won.

4
00:04:25.265 --> 00:04:26.558
I...

5
00:04:53.418 --> 00:04:54.669
What have you done?

6
00:04:59.966 --> 00:05:01.176
Jace.

7
00:05:09.935 --> 00:05:11.102
Jace.

8
00:05:13.605 --> 00:05:14.940
What have you done?

9
00:05:41.132 --> 00:05:42.467
How could you?

10
00:05:48.557 --> 00:05:51.685
How could you do this? How?

11
00:05:54.729 --> 00:05:57.399
How could you do this to me?

12
00:05:58.400 --> 00:05:59.734
You answer me!

13
00:06:05.490 --> 00:06:07.367
How could you do this?

14
00:06:08.827 --> 00:06:12.706
You answer me! Please!

15
00:06:14.165 --> 00:06:16.686
How could you do this?

16
00:06:16.710 --> 00:06:19.313
Your Grace. leave him.

17
00:06:19.337 --> 00:06:21.047
You must leave him. Your Grace.

18
00:06:22.424 --> 00:06:25.236
How dare you set
your hands on me!

19
00:06:25.260 --> 00:06:26.678
How dare you!

20
00:06:46.865 --> 00:06:48.033
My queen...

21
00:06:50.785 --> 00:06:52.704
I have failed you.

22
00:06:59.711 --> 00:07:01.254
My life must be forfeit.

23
00:07:03.924 --> 00:07:05.592
And what good would that do?

24
00:07:07.427 --> 00:07:09.220
Will it wake my son?

25
00:07:10.931 --> 00:07:15.393
Will it change the truth
of his folly and yours?

26
00:07:18.229 --> 00:07:20.207
And yours!

27
00:07:20.231 --> 00:07:22.793
All of you who knew
what Jacaerys had done

28
00:07:22.817 --> 00:07:24.879
and stood by.

29
00:07:24.903 --> 00:07:26.380
Are your lives.
too. not forfeit?

30
00:07:26.404 --> 00:07:29.467
Have you not betrayed
your queen?

31
00:08:18.164 --> 00:08:19.833
Lord Corlys!

32
00:08:35.724 --> 00:08:37.225
Lord Corlys!

33
00:08:43.523 --> 00:08:45.150
Lord Corlys!

34
00:08:55.660 --> 00:08:57.078
Whoa. calm.

35
00:09:16.347 --> 00:09:17.348
Help me.

36
00:09:18.391 --> 00:09:19.391
My lady.

37
00:09:20.518 --> 00:09:22.854
I have done a terrible thing.

38
00:09:24.230 --> 00:09:26.066
Why have you come here?

39
00:09:27.692 --> 00:09:28.794
There was a battle.

40
00:09:28.818 --> 00:09:30.904
The prince Jacaerys.
it seems. is dead.

41
00:09:36.576 --> 00:09:39.847
-You need to go now.
-Oh. there was ships and smoke.

42
00:09:39.871 --> 00:09:41.849
I wanted only to help. truly.

43
00:09:41.873 --> 00:09:44.073
-But Sheep stealer was frightened. so...
-I don't care.

44
00:09:45.877 --> 00:09:47.855
You were supposed to be
on a ship to Pentos.

45
00:09:47.879 --> 00:09:50.191
Well. I need asylum. my lady.

46
00:09:50.215 --> 00:09:53.152
-I had nowhere else to go.
-How dare you? Asylum?

47
00:09:53.176 --> 00:09:56.489
You run from my charge and
you bring disaster to my doorstep.

48
00:09:56.513 --> 00:09:59.241
-The queen will be hunting you.
-None saw that it was me.

49
00:10:01.351 --> 00:10:03.120
I would say
you had lost all sense.

50
00:10:03.144 --> 00:10:05.063
but then I doubt you had
any in the first place.

51
00:10:07.941 --> 00:10:09.275
Don't come back here.

52
00:10:12.654 --> 00:10:14.239
Do you want a dragon or not?

53
00:10:16.116 --> 00:10:17.593
You said yourself
you were deceived

54
00:10:17.617 --> 00:10:18.993
in your dealings with the queen.

55
00:10:20.078 --> 00:10:21.454
Taken for a fool.

56
00:10:23.081 --> 00:10:25.559
You wanted protection.
I offer it now.

57
00:10:32.423 --> 00:10:33.842
Vhagar is at large.

58
00:10:35.260 --> 00:10:37.780
Sheep stealer has long
made his home here.

59
00:10:37.804 --> 00:10:39.264
All we need from you...

60
00:10:40.598 --> 00:10:41.850
is blindness.

61
00:10:49.440 --> 00:10:50.942
The Vale is vast.

62
00:10:52.610 --> 00:10:55.321
I cannot stop a dragon
from abiding where it pleases.

63
00:10:57.782 --> 00:11:00.535
I do not wish to see you again.

64
00:11:06.541 --> 00:11:08.769
<i>♪ I tell a tale
of a fearsome war ♪</i>

65
00:11:08.793 --> 00:11:10.271
<i>♪ Thank our lucky stones ♪</i>

66
00:11:10.295 --> 00:11:12.523
<i>♪ 10.000 came. but we had more ♪</i>

67
00:11:12.547 --> 00:11:14.441
<i>♪ And pressed 'em
to the bloody shore ♪</i>

68
00:11:14.465 --> 00:11:16.235
<i>♪ Now we can't see
the water's floor ♪</i>

69
00:11:16.259 --> 00:11:17.778
<i>♪ Hey. hey. hey! ♪</i>

70
00:11:17.802 --> 00:11:19.363
<i>♪ 'Cause the lake's
full of their bones ♪</i>

71
00:11:21.014 --> 00:11:22.366
-Fish feed!
-Fish feed!

72
00:11:22.390 --> 00:11:24.618
-Fish feed!
-Fish feed!

73
00:11:24.642 --> 00:11:26.370
Smashed to smithereens!

74
00:11:26.394 --> 00:11:28.122
Fish feed! Fish feed!

75
00:11:28.146 --> 00:11:29.874
Fish feed!

76
00:11:29.898 --> 00:11:31.667
<i>♪ We drowned
the fucking Greens ♪</i>

77
00:11:31.691 --> 00:11:33.794
<i>♪ I tell you a tale
of a cunning trick ♪</i>

78
00:11:33.818 --> 00:11:35.296
<i>♪ How did it come to pass? ♪</i>

79
00:11:35.320 --> 00:11:37.131
<i>♪ Aemond comes.
they said. run quick! ♪</i>

80
00:11:37.155 --> 00:11:39.216
<i>♪ With his one good eye.
he looks a prick ♪</i>

81
00:11:39.240 --> 00:11:42.386
<i>♪ And we've got Daemon.
so go stick... ♪</i>

82
00:11:42.410 --> 00:11:45.014
...your dragon
up your ass!

83
00:11:45.038 --> 00:11:48.058
Ser Simon
Strong. Your Grace.

84
00:11:48.082 --> 00:11:50.168
Well. well. well.

85
00:11:51.211 --> 00:11:52.921
Reminds you of the old times.

86
00:11:54.255 --> 00:11:55.816
When the Riverlands
were ascendant.

87
00:11:55.840 --> 00:11:58.551
music and meat
and virile young men.

88
00:11:59.761 --> 00:12:01.822
And which of these delights
drew you to us

89
00:12:01.846 --> 00:12:03.490
through glade and glen?

90
00:12:03.514 --> 00:12:05.993
I bring gifts. in token
of your victories

91
00:12:06.017 --> 00:12:08.728
at the Red Fork
and on the lake shore.

92
00:12:09.729 --> 00:12:12.666
The finest wine from
House Strong's cellars.

93
00:12:12.690 --> 00:12:15.252
Whoa!

94
00:12:15.276 --> 00:12:16.527
Wine!

95
00:12:17.695 --> 00:12:19.239
And a message for you.

96
00:12:22.617 --> 00:12:23.743
From the queen.

97
00:12:43.930 --> 00:12:45.741
Your Grace?

98
00:12:45.765 --> 00:12:47.225
Is there something amiss?

99
00:12:51.938 --> 00:12:53.773
The crown prince is dead.

100
00:12:56.567 --> 00:12:58.212
I'm summoned now
to King's Landing

101
00:12:58.236 --> 00:12:59.922
to claim the Iron Throne
for our queen.

102
00:12:59.946 --> 00:13:02.633
I charge you to march south
and meet me there.

103
00:13:02.657 --> 00:13:05.427
And send men to garrison
Harrenhal. but march with strength.

104
00:13:05.451 --> 00:13:07.763
And when Rhaenyra
has claimed the Iron Throne.

105
00:13:07.787 --> 00:13:09.932
we will send dragons
to scour the skies above you.

106
00:13:09.956 --> 00:13:11.934
Be cunning. be steadfast.

107
00:13:11.958 --> 00:13:13.918
Cut down any who remain
to resist you.

108
00:13:15.461 --> 00:13:17.231
We will be the queen's fist.

109
00:13:17.255 --> 00:13:19.257
None will stand against us.

110
00:13:27.598 --> 00:13:28.933
To King's Landing!

111
00:13:30.601 --> 00:13:33.664
-And the day we meet again.
-King's Landing!

112
00:13:39.152 --> 00:13:40.671
I have seen that your coming

113
00:13:40.695 --> 00:13:42.405
has been an omen of the end.

114
00:13:43.031 --> 00:13:45.992
-The end of what?
-Many things.

115
00:13:48.995 --> 00:13:50.639
And the beginning of others.

116
00:13:50.663 --> 00:13:52.683
I would thank you for your help.
but I'm not sure yet

117
00:13:52.707 --> 00:13:54.143
what your purpose has been.

118
00:13:54.167 --> 00:13:55.769
I've done the queen a service.

119
00:13:55.793 --> 00:13:58.379
I put 40.000 river men
at her call.

120
00:13:59.714 --> 00:14:00.840
Tell her...

121
00:14:02.050 --> 00:14:03.301
I want Harrenhal.

122
00:14:05.720 --> 00:14:07.948
I've lived there
all my long life.

123
00:14:07.972 --> 00:14:10.534
and I've seen it given
from hand to hand.

124
00:14:10.558 --> 00:14:12.828
And yet none seem to cherish it.

125
00:14:12.852 --> 00:14:15.146
Why should it not come to me?

126
00:14:16.481 --> 00:14:19.293
You have neither name.
nor title.

127
00:14:19.317 --> 00:14:20.985
nor noble husband.

128
00:14:22.153 --> 00:14:23.672
The crown is not in the habit

129
00:14:23.696 --> 00:14:26.157
of giving out castles
to midwives.

130
00:14:27.658 --> 00:14:30.244
And is midwife the sum
of what you think I am?

131
00:14:35.500 --> 00:14:37.502
I will speak with her.
Perhaps there is...

132
00:14:38.628 --> 00:14:40.856
some other reward
she may extend your way.

133
00:14:40.880 --> 00:14:43.174
Some other reward?

134
00:14:45.051 --> 00:14:47.512
I ask for food
and you offer me rubies.

135
00:14:49.680 --> 00:14:51.182
For all their worth...

136
00:14:52.767 --> 00:14:55.103
they will never
satisfy my hunger.

137
00:14:57.855 --> 00:15:00.834
Go home. Daemon.

138
00:15:00.858 --> 00:15:02.777
But do not come back here.

139
00:15:04.195 --> 00:15:05.696
Remember what I told you.

140
00:15:51.075 --> 00:15:53.470
Many before have
left my grandsire for dead.

141
00:15:53.494 --> 00:15:55.663
and they were all mistaken.

142
00:15:56.581 --> 00:15:57.832
We will find him.

143
00:16:07.967 --> 00:16:08.968
Oh!

144
00:16:14.682 --> 00:16:17.161
You...

145
00:16:17.185 --> 00:16:18.936
Y-You knew him as a child.

146
00:16:21.647 --> 00:16:23.941
He was stern...

147
00:16:25.776 --> 00:16:26.944
but gentle.

148
00:16:28.112 --> 00:16:29.280
At least in my eyes.

149
00:16:30.031 --> 00:16:31.633
He loved my grandmother

150
00:16:31.657 --> 00:16:34.511
more than few men
I have seen love their wives.

151
00:16:34.535 --> 00:16:37.097
It was for her sake...

152
00:16:37.121 --> 00:16:41.209
I think. that he tried
to forget about you.

153
00:16:43.628 --> 00:16:44.879
Your brother told me.

154
00:16:48.549 --> 00:16:51.511
We were not mere memories
to be forgotten.

155
00:16:53.012 --> 00:16:54.013
No.

156
00:16:56.390 --> 00:16:58.202
He is proud as well.

157
00:16:58.226 --> 00:16:59.685
to his detriment.

158
00:17:00.645 --> 00:17:02.623
Stiff of neck.

159
00:17:05.858 --> 00:17:06.859
Ah.

160
00:17:08.069 --> 00:17:11.155
That side of him. I know.

161
00:17:12.865 --> 00:17:13.866
Knew.

162
00:17:15.159 --> 00:17:16.994
I will not say so yet.

163
00:17:24.252 --> 00:17:25.503
And your betrothed?

164
00:17:26.546 --> 00:17:28.005
We were children together.

165
00:17:31.175 --> 00:17:33.844
I'm tired
of losing people. Alyn.

166
00:17:42.186 --> 00:17:43.771
He's searching. too.

167
00:18:46.417 --> 00:18:49.086
-You seem to be in less pain.
-No. I'm not.

168
00:18:50.796 --> 00:18:52.232
You no longer ask
for milk of the poppy...

169
00:18:52.256 --> 00:18:53.984
That's because I'm not
fucking speaking to you.

170
00:18:54.008 --> 00:18:55.694
Right.

171
00:18:55.718 --> 00:18:57.321
You're still furious
that I saved your life.

172
00:18:57.345 --> 00:18:59.072
You betrayed my identity
to our captors.

173
00:18:59.096 --> 00:19:01.116
Who you needlessly
antagonized. Your Grace.

174
00:19:01.140 --> 00:19:02.767
They were going to murder you.

175
00:19:03.934 --> 00:19:05.787
You are at least now

176
00:19:05.811 --> 00:19:07.748
headed in the right direction
towards the coast.

177
00:19:07.772 --> 00:19:09.416
Yeah. and what happens
when we get there?

178
00:19:09.440 --> 00:19:10.917
When we're dragged
before Rhaenyra

179
00:19:10.941 --> 00:19:13.837
and her gloating
fucking court of cunts?

180
00:19:16.155 --> 00:19:17.323
What is it?

181
00:19:19.784 --> 00:19:20.868
What is it?

182
00:19:21.661 --> 00:19:22.846
I can see only the road
behind us.

183
00:19:22.870 --> 00:19:24.955
but I shouldn't be surprised
if there is...

184
00:19:29.794 --> 00:19:31.605
I was mistaken. I am surprised.

185
00:19:36.967 --> 00:19:38.654
That peacock Tyland Lannister

186
00:19:38.678 --> 00:19:40.447
has actually convinced
the Triarchy

187
00:19:40.471 --> 00:19:41.948
to come into it
against Rhaenyra.

188
00:19:43.307 --> 00:19:45.107
Though it doesn't seem
to have gone very well.

189
00:19:45.851 --> 00:19:47.186
Get them back inside!

190
00:19:49.855 --> 00:19:52.000
You heard him! Inside!

191
00:19:58.656 --> 00:20:00.133
It seems our journey
to Dragonstone

192
00:20:00.157 --> 00:20:02.177
will be somewhat delayed.

193
00:20:18.759 --> 00:20:20.636
Your Grace.

194
00:20:21.303 --> 00:20:23.532
You should take shelter
in the forest. and quickly.

195
00:20:23.556 --> 00:20:25.492
I have gold enough to buy our berth.

196
00:20:25.516 --> 00:20:26.868
We can make our way
to Duskendale.

197
00:20:26.892 --> 00:20:28.352
We are going to Rook's Rest.

198
00:20:29.562 --> 00:20:31.957
We would be wise to avoid that
place. We could be captured again.

199
00:20:31.981 --> 00:20:33.875
Cole has a garrison there.
does he not?

200
00:20:33.899 --> 00:20:36.002
-They will be loyal to me.
-But the road there. Your Grace.

201
00:20:36.026 --> 00:20:37.361
is long and perilous.

202
00:20:44.034 --> 00:20:45.786
If this be victory...

203
00:20:46.871 --> 00:20:48.372
I hope I never see another.

204
00:21:05.890 --> 00:21:08.267
Alyn. I have nothing
to give you now.

205
00:21:09.393 --> 00:21:10.895
But my name.

206
00:21:22.823 --> 00:21:26.452
And yet I count that
of more worth...

207
00:21:27.828 --> 00:21:29.455
than a mountain of gold.

208
00:22:08.452 --> 00:22:10.454
I would speak with
Commander Largent.

209
00:22:16.836 --> 00:22:18.462
Then speak. Your Grace.

210
00:22:21.882 --> 00:22:24.552
I regret intruding
on your Gold Cloaks. but...

211
00:22:26.679 --> 00:22:28.389
the matter is grave.

212
00:22:29.807 --> 00:22:31.034
If word were to seep out.

213
00:22:31.058 --> 00:22:32.643
it would spell death
for all involved.

214
00:22:38.983 --> 00:22:40.860
Rhaenyra is returning.

215
00:22:43.654 --> 00:22:45.215
How come you by this knowledge?

216
00:22:45.239 --> 00:22:46.716
In the prince regent's absence.

217
00:22:46.740 --> 00:22:49.076
Queen Helaena holds
the authority of the city.

218
00:22:50.119 --> 00:22:51.638
She intends.
in the interest of peace.

219
00:22:51.662 --> 00:22:53.723
to allow Rhaenyra
to enter the Red Keep.

220
00:22:53.747 --> 00:22:56.393
and to then take the throne.

221
00:22:56.417 --> 00:22:58.502
-Some would call that treason.
-Some would.

222
00:23:00.754 --> 00:23:02.381
The question is. would you?

223
00:23:29.366 --> 00:23:31.035
The Rogue Prince himself.

224
00:23:36.874 --> 00:23:38.208
What are you doing here?

225
00:23:39.376 --> 00:23:40.854
My prince.

226
00:23:40.878 --> 00:23:42.772
We are just returned
from Harrenhal.

227
00:23:42.796 --> 00:23:44.381
And-and the Gullet.

228
00:23:45.090 --> 00:23:48.052
Uh. we weren't sure
if we should go up there.

229
00:23:49.637 --> 00:23:51.221
A terrible thing has happened.

230
00:23:53.223 --> 00:23:55.392
The queen wished you
to attack or pursue Vhagar.

231
00:23:57.770 --> 00:23:59.063
Or am I mistaken?

232
00:23:59.897 --> 00:24:02.232
Aemond did not come.

233
00:24:04.234 --> 00:24:07.655
And you waited two days only
before resigning your mission?

234
00:24:08.489 --> 00:24:12.242
-Addam left. too.
-We thought there might be some misunderstanding.

235
00:24:13.744 --> 00:24:16.097
I was unaware Her Grace.
the queen. had required of you

236
00:24:16.121 --> 00:24:20.000
in this moment. or any other.
your thoughts.

237
00:24:23.462 --> 00:24:25.899
There's something wrong
in those woods. though.

238
00:24:25.923 --> 00:24:26.966
I'm telling you.

239
00:24:27.967 --> 00:24:29.736
We heard all kinds of sounds.

240
00:24:29.760 --> 00:24:31.237
like voices. I saw a...

241
00:24:36.141 --> 00:24:38.578
You have erred.

242
00:24:38.602 --> 00:24:40.580
All three of you. and your
error will cost us dearly.

243
00:24:40.604 --> 00:24:42.374
I left a garrison there.
and a household.

244
00:24:42.398 --> 00:24:45.502
There was a woman
who brought news of a battle.

245
00:24:45.526 --> 00:24:46.920
A maester. I thought.

246
00:24:46.944 --> 00:24:48.505
Or...

247
00:24:48.529 --> 00:24:50.155
maybe a witch.

248
00:24:52.491 --> 00:24:54.427
-Where is your comrade?
-He's gone with the Lady Baela

249
00:24:54.451 --> 00:24:55.619
back to the Gullet.

250
00:25:00.958 --> 00:25:03.520
Should we return now
to Harrenhal. my prince?

251
00:25:18.559 --> 00:25:19.810
Is she inside?

252
00:25:20.811 --> 00:25:23.373
She has not wished
to be seen since Jace.

253
00:25:23.397 --> 00:25:25.458
Ah. And meanwhile.

254
00:25:25.482 --> 00:25:27.794
the smith and the sot
allow Aemond One-Eye

255
00:25:27.818 --> 00:25:30.046
-to fly through their fingers.
-She is in grief.

256
00:25:30.070 --> 00:25:31.989
-Do you question her methods?
-Not hers.

257
00:25:32.990 --> 00:25:34.718
Theirs.

258
00:25:34.742 --> 00:25:35.826
And yours.

259
00:25:36.910 --> 00:25:38.471
I left you here a prisoner.

260
00:25:38.495 --> 00:25:41.349
Having forsaken the promise
that you made to me.

261
00:25:41.373 --> 00:25:44.185
You've wriggled your way
toward the crown like an eel.

262
00:25:44.209 --> 00:25:47.480
I confess. I underestimated
your slipperiness.

263
00:25:47.504 --> 00:25:50.233
Bait me all you wish.

264
00:25:50.257 --> 00:25:53.987
I have the queen's trust.
which you have yet to earn.

265
00:25:54.011 --> 00:25:56.322
-The queen is my wife.
-Then why have you added

266
00:25:56.346 --> 00:25:57.907
to what she must already suffer?

267
00:25:57.931 --> 00:25:59.767
What is between us
is none of your concern.

268
00:26:01.518 --> 00:26:02.895
What game are you playing?

269
00:26:03.896 --> 00:26:07.024
Retribution for insults.
real or imagined?

270
00:26:08.734 --> 00:26:11.737
Do you coil yourself here
in order to strike at me?

271
00:26:13.572 --> 00:26:16.575
Not everything
is about you. Daemon.

272
00:26:29.379 --> 00:26:31.924
Aemond is unaccounted for. then.

273
00:26:46.980 --> 00:26:49.918
Do you believe the queen's
judgment to be sound?

274
00:26:49.942 --> 00:26:51.902
I would not serve her otherwise.

275
00:26:53.153 --> 00:26:56.466
But she has staked much on
the word of Alicent Hightower.

276
00:26:56.490 --> 00:26:57.950
Hm. aye.

277
00:26:59.159 --> 00:27:00.619
I was not present
at their meeting.

278
00:27:01.620 --> 00:27:04.248
They were girls together.
as all know.

279
00:27:05.415 --> 00:27:08.228
Do you believe.
after what has since transpired.

280
00:27:08.252 --> 00:27:10.587
that there is some bond
between them still?

281
00:27:11.588 --> 00:27:12.589
Perhaps.

282
00:27:14.925 --> 00:27:16.176
Would that pain you?

283
00:27:18.095 --> 00:27:21.574
My concern
is for the queen only.

284
00:27:21.598 --> 00:27:23.326
I'm no friend to the Hightowers.

285
00:27:23.350 --> 00:27:25.411
Well. there we are agreed.
though I believe Alicent

286
00:27:25.435 --> 00:27:27.330
is by nature a conspirator

287
00:27:27.354 --> 00:27:29.439
rather than one
who openly deceives.

288
00:27:30.315 --> 00:27:32.585
Or perhaps a tool.

289
00:27:32.609 --> 00:27:34.295
Begging your pardon. my prince.

290
00:27:34.319 --> 00:27:36.464
It seems Vhagar has been sighted

291
00:27:36.488 --> 00:27:37.823
leaving King's Landing...

292
00:27:38.866 --> 00:27:42.178
flying in the direction
of the Riverlands.

293
00:27:42.202 --> 00:27:44.305
I would inform
the queen. but. uh...

294
00:27:44.329 --> 00:27:45.849
I will go.

295
00:28:01.638 --> 00:28:02.758
Your Grace!

296
00:28:03.974 --> 00:28:06.018
The atmosphere is fraught.

297
00:28:09.021 --> 00:28:12.566
I think it's best you do not
stray again from my charge.

298
00:28:13.317 --> 00:28:15.503
I would speak with the captain of
the household guard. Ser Soren.

299
00:28:15.527 --> 00:28:16.546
Where might he be?

300
00:28:16.570 --> 00:28:18.197
Any number of places.

301
00:28:19.656 --> 00:28:21.968
-I could have a message sent to him.
-Thank you. no.

302
00:28:21.992 --> 00:28:24.554
Please make sure that the
small council chamber is secure.

303
00:28:24.578 --> 00:28:26.514
-I will call a meeting there presently.
-Your Grace?

304
00:28:26.538 --> 00:28:27.915
I command it.

305
00:28:29.166 --> 00:28:30.977
At once. Ser Rickard.

306
00:28:31.001 --> 00:28:32.544
As you wish.

307
00:28:39.176 --> 00:28:41.094
He died
fighting for his queen.

308
00:28:42.846 --> 00:28:44.389
As was his desire.

309
00:28:47.100 --> 00:28:48.602
He defied me.

310
00:28:51.188 --> 00:28:52.689
That is what sons do.

311
00:28:55.567 --> 00:28:57.194
There was another dragon.

312
00:28:58.695 --> 00:29:00.715
Sheep stealer. Baela says.

313
00:29:00.739 --> 00:29:02.032
A wild dragon?

314
00:29:03.200 --> 00:29:04.618
He had a rider.

315
00:29:06.578 --> 00:29:08.890
That's impossible. A wild
dragon cannot ever be tamed.

316
00:29:08.914 --> 00:29:10.850
They attacked Moondancer

317
00:29:10.874 --> 00:29:12.542
and drew Jace to his death.

318
00:29:13.877 --> 00:29:15.730
How can the Greens
have claimed another?

319
00:29:15.754 --> 00:29:17.881
-I want you to find them.
-It will be done.

320
00:29:24.763 --> 00:29:27.116
But there is first
more pressing business.

321
00:29:27.140 --> 00:29:28.725
No. I have no stomach for it.

322
00:29:32.771 --> 00:29:34.606
Vhagar has left King's Landing.

323
00:29:52.958 --> 00:29:55.002
The boys who...

324
00:29:56.628 --> 00:29:58.088
clung to me. who...

325
00:30:00.173 --> 00:30:03.152
hid their little faces
in my skirts. dead.

326
00:30:03.176 --> 00:30:06.596
so that I may sit
upon a throne of swords?

327
00:30:12.477 --> 00:30:14.146
Will you let them die in vain?

328
00:30:42.341 --> 00:30:43.508
No. no.

329
00:31:12.037 --> 00:31:13.038
Well.

330
00:31:16.083 --> 00:31:17.518
I beg your pardon?

331
00:31:17.542 --> 00:31:20.521
What an industrious
little creature you are.

332
00:31:20.545 --> 00:31:22.690
Hither and thither.
So much to do.

333
00:31:22.714 --> 00:31:24.734
You would do well to
remember yourself. Lord Jasper.

334
00:31:24.758 --> 00:31:27.094
I remember myself well enough.

335
00:31:27.928 --> 00:31:30.156
I remember you. too. Your Grace.

336
00:31:30.180 --> 00:31:32.450
snaking your way
into the halls of power

337
00:31:32.474 --> 00:31:33.850
when you were just a girl.

338
00:31:35.394 --> 00:31:36.603
So young.

339
00:31:38.438 --> 00:31:40.023
So bold.

340
00:31:42.651 --> 00:31:45.671
I served Viserys faithfully.
I served this realm faithfully.

341
00:31:45.695 --> 00:31:47.531
You did what you had to do.

342
00:31:48.865 --> 00:31:50.534
No man could deny you that.

343
00:31:54.121 --> 00:31:57.058
Life is short.
The gods are cruel.

344
00:31:57.082 --> 00:32:00.228
We all find what
enjoyment we can

345
00:32:00.252 --> 00:32:02.045
as the world
heads into darkness.

346
00:32:05.882 --> 00:32:08.385
You... for instance.

347
00:32:11.513 --> 00:32:14.391
You found much enjoyment.

348
00:32:17.310 --> 00:32:18.645
With Ser Criston.

349
00:32:20.397 --> 00:32:22.065
-Did you not?
-Lord...

350
00:32:22.899 --> 00:32:24.127
Lord Jasper.

351
00:32:24.151 --> 00:32:26.212
Much...

352
00:32:26.236 --> 00:32:27.463
pleasure.

353
00:32:27.487 --> 00:32:29.382
The penalty for this
would be death.

354
00:32:29.406 --> 00:32:30.883
Then what is the penalty
for you running off

355
00:32:30.907 --> 00:32:32.301
to a secret meeting
with the City Watch?

356
00:32:32.325 --> 00:32:34.220
What was your business there.
I wonder?

357
00:32:34.244 --> 00:32:35.328
Lord Jasper. please.

358
00:32:36.496 --> 00:32:38.915
-Say that again.
-What?

359
00:32:40.250 --> 00:32:41.769
Plead with me.

360
00:32:43.253 --> 00:32:44.337
No!

361
00:32:57.601 --> 00:33:00.270
No! No!

362
00:33:01.229 --> 00:33:03.273
No! No!

363
00:33:04.608 --> 00:33:06.752
No! No!

364
00:33:06.776 --> 00:33:07.861
No!

365
00:33:11.281 --> 00:33:12.425
Lord Jasper.

366
00:33:16.453 --> 00:33:18.705
Orwyle...

367
00:33:19.456 --> 00:33:20.457
Good.

368
00:33:21.625 --> 00:33:23.460
Seems we have a traitor
on our hands.

369
00:33:24.461 --> 00:33:26.063
I was just going to call
for you. Ser Soren.

370
00:33:26.087 --> 00:33:28.608
She'll need to be confined where
she can make no further trouble.

371
00:33:28.632 --> 00:33:30.276
Grand Maester.
I... I beseech you.

372
00:33:30.300 --> 00:33:31.980
Ask her where
she was an hour ago.

373
00:33:33.345 --> 00:33:36.199
I know not where
she may have been.

374
00:33:36.223 --> 00:33:39.285
But I know what I have seen
here with my own eyes.

375
00:33:39.309 --> 00:33:40.661
Arrest him!

376
00:33:40.685 --> 00:33:43.289
He dares lay his hands
on the mother of the king!

377
00:33:43.313 --> 00:33:45.875
The queen dowager
has betrayed us.

378
00:33:45.899 --> 00:33:48.211
Her own sworn protector
has cautioned me.

379
00:33:48.235 --> 00:33:49.962
You will come with us.
Lord Jasper.

380
00:33:49.986 --> 00:33:53.031
I am the Master of Laws.
for the sake of the gods.

381
00:33:54.074 --> 00:33:55.492
Unhand me!

382
00:34:03.667 --> 00:34:05.835
I'm in your debt. Grand Maester.

383
00:34:08.380 --> 00:34:10.715
I do not know what you
have done. Your Grace.

384
00:34:11.550 --> 00:34:13.510
I fear it is something
desperate.

385
00:34:34.364 --> 00:34:36.199
Our deepest condolences.
Your Grace.

386
00:34:37.534 --> 00:34:40.245
This... this tragic
turn of events.

387
00:34:43.623 --> 00:34:45.750
I am going
to King's Landing now.

388
00:34:46.459 --> 00:34:47.979
What? Your... Your Grace.
you cannot mean...

389
00:34:48.003 --> 00:34:49.939
I heard no ambiguity in
the queen's statement.

390
00:34:49.963 --> 00:34:51.899
Lord Bartimos. did you?

391
00:34:51.923 --> 00:34:53.901
I will fly with my lord husband

392
00:34:53.925 --> 00:34:55.695
and with my new riders
as guards.

393
00:34:55.719 --> 00:34:58.614
That is all very well.
but you cannot enter the castle

394
00:34:58.638 --> 00:35:01.033
on your dragon. my queen.

395
00:35:01.057 --> 00:35:03.244
The Velaryon host is scattered.

396
00:35:03.268 --> 00:35:05.288
You will not have them
to defend you.

397
00:35:05.312 --> 00:35:06.706
She has me.

398
00:35:06.730 --> 00:35:09.917
Aemond flies to Harrenhal
as Alicent promised.

399
00:35:09.941 --> 00:35:11.711
When he returns.
our window will shut.

400
00:35:11.735 --> 00:35:13.462
For... forgive me. my queen.

401
00:35:13.486 --> 00:35:16.632
but this reeks of a snare.

402
00:35:16.656 --> 00:35:18.950
If it is. so be it.
I'm done with talking.

403
00:35:22.412 --> 00:35:24.789
Let Ser Lorent
choose how he will die.

404
00:35:31.630 --> 00:35:33.256
You will need this. I think.

405
00:35:38.261 --> 00:35:40.180
I hope you will send for me.

406
00:35:43.642 --> 00:35:45.935
Remember which one of us
has been faithful.

407
00:36:04.454 --> 00:36:07.183
Much has
changed since I was away.

408
00:36:07.207 --> 00:36:08.643
You've taken a new advisor.

409
00:36:08.667 --> 00:36:11.437
She's done much for us.

410
00:36:11.461 --> 00:36:13.939
-For me.
-So I gather.

411
00:36:13.963 --> 00:36:15.816
I have no need of your approval.

412
00:36:15.840 --> 00:36:18.301
It was an observation.

413
00:36:21.763 --> 00:36:23.807
My prince. Your Grace.

414
00:36:27.644 --> 00:36:28.812
Syrax!

415
00:36:37.320 --> 00:36:39.656
Today. King's Landing
receives its queen.

416
00:36:41.157 --> 00:36:43.302
You will fly cover.
Stay wide and keep watch.

417
00:36:43.326 --> 00:36:44.679
Let none approach from the sky.

418
00:36:44.703 --> 00:36:46.663
Is that simple enough for you?

419
00:36:47.997 --> 00:36:49.392
It is.

420
00:36:49.416 --> 00:36:51.185
Stay on guard until I send word.

421
00:36:51.209 --> 00:36:53.312
It will not at any point
be necessary for you

422
00:36:53.336 --> 00:36:54.814
to engage in thinking.

423
00:36:54.838 --> 00:36:58.383
or making decisions.
or having ideas.

424
00:37:00.677 --> 00:37:03.346
-No. Your Grace.
-No.

425
00:37:05.098 --> 00:37:06.367
Once the city is taken.

426
00:37:06.391 --> 00:37:07.934
we return our attention
to Vhagar.

427
00:37:09.978 --> 00:37:12.689
From this moment. all must
proceed according to plan.

428
00:37:16.526 --> 00:37:18.069
Don't let me down.

429
00:37:51.728 --> 00:37:54.063
Helaena. Helaena.

430
00:37:55.607 --> 00:37:58.544
This is strange.
It isn't the season.

431
00:37:58.568 --> 00:38:00.588
Rhaenyra Is coming.

432
00:38:00.612 --> 00:38:03.424
-I need you now.
-Will there be a battle?

433
00:38:03.448 --> 00:38:04.925
No. No.

434
00:38:04.949 --> 00:38:08.137
We will allow her to enter.
and then we will flee.

435
00:38:08.161 --> 00:38:10.079
You've spoken to her?

436
00:38:11.414 --> 00:38:12.725
But I've been delayed.

437
00:38:12.749 --> 00:38:14.584
It seems Ser Rickard
has betrayed me.

438
00:38:15.668 --> 00:38:17.396
We must stand down
the sentries on the battlement

439
00:38:17.420 --> 00:38:18.939
and as many of the household
guards as we are able.

440
00:38:18.963 --> 00:38:22.318
-They will think you mad.
-But they will heed a queen.

441
00:38:22.342 --> 00:38:24.570
You are a queen.

442
00:38:24.594 --> 00:38:26.280
Helena. you are <i>the</i> queen.

443
00:38:26.304 --> 00:38:27.764
Quickly.

444
00:38:28.848 --> 00:38:30.767
You said my father
changed his mind.

445
00:38:31.684 --> 00:38:34.079
You made Aegon king.
you and Ser Criston

446
00:38:34.103 --> 00:38:36.290
and my grandsire.
and the septon.

447
00:38:36.314 --> 00:38:38.250
I made a mistake.

448
00:38:38.274 --> 00:38:40.294
-But you heard him.
-If I did or I didn't.

449
00:38:40.318 --> 00:38:42.862
I could no longer say.
But Helaena...

450
00:38:44.030 --> 00:38:46.175
you told me not many days ago

451
00:38:46.199 --> 00:38:47.951
that you were happier
before you were queen.

452
00:38:48.785 --> 00:38:50.537
Words that pierced me
like a spear.

453
00:38:52.288 --> 00:38:54.767
I think now not of what
you may deserve.

454
00:38:54.791 --> 00:38:57.043
but what might make you happy.

455
00:38:58.461 --> 00:39:00.463
You. I may yet redeem.

456
00:39:06.219 --> 00:39:09.222
I think I might like
to keep chickens.

457
00:39:17.397 --> 00:39:19.190
-My queen.
-Your Grace.

458
00:39:21.943 --> 00:39:23.212
-Your Grace.
-My queen.

459
00:39:23.236 --> 00:39:24.630
You.

460
00:39:24.654 --> 00:39:26.823
-Who's your captain?
-Ser Freddryk. Your Grace.

461
00:39:32.036 --> 00:39:33.472
Is aught amiss. Your Grace?

462
00:39:33.496 --> 00:39:35.683
You are to stand down
your station. Ser Freddryk.

463
00:39:35.707 --> 00:39:37.667
at the command
of the Queen Helaena.

464
00:39:39.502 --> 00:39:41.522
Standing orders. Your Grace.

465
00:39:41.546 --> 00:39:43.148
Any dragon but Vhagar.
we strike.

466
00:39:43.172 --> 00:39:45.192
Your orders are rescinded.

467
00:39:45.216 --> 00:39:48.696
-But the prince regent...
-The prince regent has left the city.

468
00:39:48.720 --> 00:39:50.847
The queen is your authority now.

469
00:39:52.098 --> 00:39:54.267
I will not have
any beast harmed.

470
00:39:58.146 --> 00:40:00.523
Rhaenyra Targaryen approaches.
Ser Freddryk.

471
00:40:01.691 --> 00:40:04.027
She comes with Prince Daemon
and more besides.

472
00:40:04.944 --> 00:40:06.255
The king has abdicated.

473
00:40:06.279 --> 00:40:08.573
The prince regent himself
has fled the city.

474
00:40:09.532 --> 00:40:11.385
Will you fight and be burned.

475
00:40:11.409 --> 00:40:13.095
and King's Landing
along with you. or

476
00:40:13.119 --> 00:40:15.764
will you suffer her to enter.
and hope for peace?

477
00:40:15.788 --> 00:40:17.707
Her sons were always kind.

478
00:40:21.544 --> 00:40:22.754
Ser Freddryk.

479
00:40:58.247 --> 00:40:59.457
To Harrenhal.

480
00:41:00.416 --> 00:41:03.062
To Harrenhal!

481
00:41:43.626 --> 00:41:45.837
Dragon!

482
00:43:27.980 --> 00:43:29.941
I seek Daemon Targaryen.

483
00:43:31.400 --> 00:43:33.402
I confess. we had not been
expecting you.

484
00:43:36.114 --> 00:43:37.466
Draw your sword.

485
00:43:39.033 --> 00:43:41.744
-Your Grace. I have no sword.
-Then get one!

486
00:43:45.456 --> 00:43:47.333
I do not wish to oppose you.

487
00:43:52.255 --> 00:43:54.757
I have not wielded a blade
these many years.

488
00:43:56.467 --> 00:44:00.263
Surely. there is some other
way you might find satisfaction?

489
00:44:00.847 --> 00:44:02.265
Hm?

490
00:44:05.768 --> 00:44:07.353
The army has decamped.

491
00:44:09.814 --> 00:44:11.917
There's nothing to stop you.

492
00:44:20.616 --> 00:44:21.784
Father!

493
00:45:35.233 --> 00:45:36.525
Help me.

494
00:45:41.197 --> 00:45:42.740
Help me...

495
00:48:02.838 --> 00:48:04.507
Alicent did as she promised.

496
00:48:06.509 --> 00:48:08.511
The true test is within.

497
00:48:11.680 --> 00:48:13.182
Do not be afraid.

498
00:48:15.684 --> 00:48:17.371
I've come to make things right.

499
00:48:46.215 --> 00:48:48.884
Wait.

500
00:49:20.416 --> 00:49:23.794
Who else dares rise
against us in our house?

501
00:50:04.877 --> 00:50:06.629
Your Grace.

502
00:50:37.701 --> 00:50:39.328
Halt!

503
00:50:47.002 --> 00:50:48.480
Where is Aegon?

504
00:50:48.504 --> 00:50:50.482
It is nothing to you.

505
00:50:50.506 --> 00:50:51.816
I have business with him.

506
00:50:51.840 --> 00:50:54.653
Is the upstart pup too craven
to face his queen?

507
00:50:54.677 --> 00:50:56.887
You are brazen.
I credit you this.

508
00:50:57.930 --> 00:50:59.223
Brazen or thick.

509
00:51:01.225 --> 00:51:03.435
I suppose that depends
whether I win or lose.

510
00:51:07.356 --> 00:51:09.358
Now here's a thing
I haven't seen before.

511
00:51:19.034 --> 00:51:20.578
Stay close. Rhaenyra.

512
00:51:40.723 --> 00:51:42.701
Well met...

513
00:51:42.725 --> 00:51:43.892
Ser Luthor.

514
00:51:46.061 --> 00:51:49.148
The City Watch remembers our
commander. Daemon Targaryen...

515
00:51:50.649 --> 00:51:52.627
and Queen Rhaenyra.

516
00:51:52.651 --> 00:51:54.903
the one true heir
to the Iron Throne.

517
00:51:57.239 --> 00:51:59.718
The guards at the gates
have thrown down their swords.

518
00:51:59.742 --> 00:52:03.078
Do the same.
or perish as traitors.

519
00:52:22.139 --> 00:52:25.076
The prince regent
will not stand for this.

520
00:52:25.100 --> 00:52:27.019
-Nor will the Hand!
-Seize them!

521
00:52:29.813 --> 00:52:33.108
And with them all who wear
the Hightower sigil.

522
00:52:41.492 --> 00:52:43.619
You have my gratitude.
Ser Luthor.

523
00:52:44.536 --> 00:52:47.956
It was Prince Daemon himself
who gave me this gold cloak...

524
00:52:49.291 --> 00:52:51.686
20 years ago.

525
00:52:51.710 --> 00:52:53.313
I knew I'd see you
again one day.

526
00:52:55.005 --> 00:52:57.045
I wish I could say
I was so sure about you.

527
00:53:04.306 --> 00:53:05.974
It's your throne. my queen.

528
00:53:07.434 --> 00:53:08.811
Not yet.

529
00:53:10.854 --> 00:53:12.314
Bring Aegon...

530
00:53:13.357 --> 00:53:14.733
the Usurper...

531
00:53:15.859 --> 00:53:17.837
to me!

532
00:53:42.344 --> 00:53:44.155
-He is not here.
-Then where?

533
00:53:44.179 --> 00:53:45.514
I do not know.

534
00:53:46.348 --> 00:53:48.326
I swear it.

535
00:53:48.350 --> 00:53:49.911
He is fled.

536
00:53:49.935 --> 00:53:51.830
and the Master of Whisperers
with him.

537
00:53:51.854 --> 00:53:53.081
How convenient.

538
00:53:53.105 --> 00:53:55.607
I remained here when Aegon
took the throne.

539
00:53:56.734 --> 00:53:58.610
I am no knight.
I feared for my life.

540
00:53:59.653 --> 00:54:02.382
But I've done what I can. as
the queen dowager can attest.

541
00:54:02.406 --> 00:54:03.699
She's not here either.

542
00:54:06.368 --> 00:54:11.224
I pledge fealty
to Viserys' rightful heir.

543
00:54:11.248 --> 00:54:13.542
queen by blood and by oath.

544
00:54:20.048 --> 00:54:23.778
If the Usurper has fled. then we
must take heads. as you well know.

545
00:54:23.802 --> 00:54:26.281
loath as I am
to strike down a maester.

546
00:54:26.305 --> 00:54:28.056
You will kill me if you must.

547
00:54:30.225 --> 00:54:32.728
But I can offer you another
who might give you better...

548
00:54:33.896 --> 00:54:35.397
satisfaction.

549
00:54:50.496 --> 00:54:52.080
We cannot escape this way.

550
00:55:03.425 --> 00:55:05.469
-Release them.
-At once. my prince.

551
00:55:12.518 --> 00:55:14.895
-What has happened?
-Orwyle's offered you up.

552
00:55:15.979 --> 00:55:19.417
Delightful to witness you
turning on each other like spiders.

553
00:55:19.441 --> 00:55:22.962
This is her doing.
Conniving little bitch.

554
00:55:22.986 --> 00:55:24.756
Keep talking and I'll
relieve you of your cock

555
00:55:24.780 --> 00:55:27.258
before your head.
just for the fun of it.

556
00:55:27.282 --> 00:55:28.951
If you would. my prince.

557
00:55:31.870 --> 00:55:34.682
A gift for you

558
00:55:34.706 --> 00:55:36.291
if you ever returned.

559
00:55:37.459 --> 00:55:39.461
From Lord Larys Strong.

560
00:56:35.434 --> 00:56:38.121
Lord Merry weather
and Lady Fell.

561
00:56:38.145 --> 00:56:40.397
imprisoned for holding
to their oaths. Your Grace.

562
00:56:42.065 --> 00:56:45.086
-Ah. Lady Fell.
-My queen.

563
00:56:45.110 --> 00:56:47.255
Lord Merry weather.
You have my gratitude.

564
00:56:47.279 --> 00:56:48.715
Mm.

565
00:56:48.739 --> 00:56:51.259
The Master of Laws.

566
00:56:51.283 --> 00:56:53.177
who plotted with the Usurper.

567
00:56:53.201 --> 00:56:55.513
You will hang for this!

568
00:56:55.537 --> 00:56:58.016
If you do not burn.

569
00:56:58.040 --> 00:56:59.750
Who of your council
is left alive?

570
00:57:00.959 --> 00:57:02.687
The rats in the Black Cells

571
00:57:02.711 --> 00:57:04.898
have grown uncommon big.

572
00:57:20.145 --> 00:57:22.540
No more than I expected.

573
00:57:38.455 --> 00:57:39.957
Kneel.

574
00:57:50.258 --> 00:57:52.761
I assume everyone else is dead.

575
00:57:56.515 --> 00:57:59.601
Aegon has fled. but our old
friend can stand in his place.

576
00:58:05.607 --> 00:58:07.818
Just get it over with. will you?

577
00:58:11.113 --> 00:58:12.447
They're watching.

578
00:58:23.875 --> 00:58:27.021
If you wish to rule.
show them you do not waver.

579
00:58:27.045 --> 00:58:28.839
I don't know if I can.

580
00:58:31.967 --> 00:58:33.385
Let Daemon do it.

581
00:58:37.347 --> 00:58:39.474
Spare me at least
from being hacked at.

582
00:59:01.496 --> 00:59:03.707
If your father could see
what it's come to...

583
00:59:04.750 --> 00:59:06.477
he would never have imagined it.

584
00:59:06.501 --> 00:59:07.753
Speak no more!

585
00:59:14.718 --> 00:59:17.846
In this moment.
you will become queen.

586
00:59:57.552 --> 00:59:58.863
I did my best...

587
01:00:23.745 --> 01:00:24.931
Tell my lady wife whatever...

588
01:02:05.096 --> 01:02:06.890
Clear!

589
01:02:08.391 --> 01:02:09.392
Clear!

590
01:02:10.352 --> 01:02:11.728
Stand aside!

590
